From adae00ee2338cf60ad537fd748d5c3cb202a1e9f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 11:06:45 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 8.5: Monaco-backed diff views
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replaces the hand-rolled <div>-based unified-diff renderer with embedded
Monaco DiffEditorWidgets in both the Diff sub-mode and Tour mini-diffs.
Headline win: real syntax highlighting via TextMate grammars + intra-line
word-level diff colouring, plus a foundation for LSP hover / go-to-def
once Phase 8.6's workspace registry feeds real file:// URIs.

- krtPatchReconstruct.ts — pure module that walks a unified-diff patch
  and returns { base, head } strings with empty-line padding so model
  line numbers map directly to real file line numbers. Monaco's
  hideUnchangedRegions option compresses the padded gaps in the UI.
- krtMonacoDiff.ts — KrtMonacoDiffView class. Owns two virtual
  text models (krt-pr-base://owner/repo/sha/path and krt-pr-head://...)
  and a DiffEditorWidget. Auto-sizes the container to getContentHeight
  capped at 2000px. Exposes addLineZone({ side, afterLine, domNode })
  for inline review comments + the composer, plus onLineNumberClick
  for the comment-trigger affordance.
- krtPullRequestEditorPane.ts — diff sub-mode and tour mini-diffs both
  swap their parsePatch + per-line DOM rendering for KrtMonacoDiffView.
  Inline review-comment threads + the composer become Monaco view zones
  instead of DOM siblings of patch lines. Composer trigger moves from
  per-line "+" buttons to line-number clicks (more native to Monaco).
- Cleanup: drop PatchLine, parsePatch, HUNK_HEADER_RE, renderPatchLine.
